BARCELONA coach Ernesto Valverde has announced his 23-man squad that will travel to South Africa to face Mamelodi Sundowns in a Nelson Mandela Centenary Celebration friendly match. The match is scheduled for Wednesday, 16 May at FNB Stadium 6.15 pm. Barça boss has left beind injured Samuel Umtiti and Thomas Vermaelen, but is taking three players from Barça B in addition to the other 20 members of the first team. The full list of players travelling to Mzansi are: Ter Stegen, Cillessen, Semedo, Piqué, Rakitic, Sergio Busquets, Denis Suárez, Iniesta, Luis Suárez, Messi, Dembélé, Coutinho, Paulinho, Paco Alcácer, Jordi Alba, Digne, Sergi Roberto, André Gomes, Aleix Vidal,  Yerry Mina, Carles Aleñá (26), Iñigo Ruiz de Galarreta (40) and Jorge Cuenca (41). Before heading to the airport, the players worked out on the Tito Vilanova field at the Ciutat Esportiva Joan Gamper, with Leo Messi working out in isolation and the three aforesaid reserves plus David Costas joining in too.  